what does it mean to have your work cut out for you i hear it all the time but never figureed out what it means it's a funny turn of phrase it means that the work ahead of you will be difficult and time consuming the job you've been assigned to do is a clear cut and challenging one also it insinuates that there is little time to complete the task at hand there's a bit about the history of the idiom here if you're interested http everything com index pl node id Social rule Conspiracy (TNG episode) Little Britain One Tree Hill (TV series) The Shining (film) The Big Goodbye (TNG episode) Scenes from a Memory Milton H. Erickson Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Salad Fingers Humphrey Bogart Friends New York Giants K' Jon Secada EastEnders Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 The Ashlee Simpson Show Rose (Doctor Who) The Inside Haven (TNG episode) Muslim ibn Aqeel Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Datalore (TNG episode) Piccolo Junior Saga Blood on the Tracks The Amber Spyglass Episodes of Lost (Season 2) Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) 11001001 (TNG episode) Time Out of Mind The Dalek Invasion of Earth Pitaten Angel One (TNG episode) Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban The Wizard of Oz (1939 film) Ocean's Twelve Have I Got News For You Escape from New York Knots Landing Joke Cliff Richard AFI 100 Years series Avenue Q Sharon Tate Kodocha Professional wrestling match types Rowan & Martin's Laugh-In Coming of Age (TNG episode) About a Boy Sin City The Star Wars Holiday Special Blonde on Blonde Boom Town (Doctor Who) Happy Tree Friends Jam (TV series) Darth Vader God Emperor of Dune Days of our Lives StarCraft: Uprising G-Man (Half-Life) Father's Day (Doctor Who) The Empty Child The Death Gate Cycle W.I.T.C.H. The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe We'll Always Have Paris (TNG episode) Paul Is Dead 1957 World Series Columbine High School massacre Professional wrestling throws Ned's Declassified School Survival Guide Characters of Naruto YuYu Hakusho 2005 tr